election_record.label: New York 1818 State Senate, Western District

sub_unit.name: Broome
sub_unit.note: David E. Evans received 1 vote as Daniel E. Evans.

sub_unit.name: Cayuga
sub_unit.note: Jonathan Richmond and Caleb Baker were were candidates for U.S. House of Representatives.

sub_unit.name: Genoa
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 1 vote as S. Payne.

sub_unit.name: Owasco
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 25 votes as Samuel S. Paine.

sub_unit.name: Gerry
sub_unit.note: The Chautaque Gazette, May 5, lists no votes for Perry G. Childs.

sub_unit.name: Cortland
sub_unit.note: 5 votes for David Evans were initially listed as being for Daniel Evans in the Original Election Returns. but they were corrected or changed prior to the Official Statewide Canvass.
The Cortland Republican (Cortland, NY), May 9, lists 274 votes for Perry G. Childs.

sub_unit.name: Preble
sub_unit.note: 57 votes for Perry G. Childs were recorded at the Preble Town Meeting after the election, though the original election returns list 67 votes for Childs.

sub_unit.name: Solon
sub_unit.note: Gamaliel H. Barstow received 5 votes as Gamaliel E. Barstow.

sub_unit.name: Madison
sub_unit.note: Myron Holly received 1 vote as Myron Hawley.

sub_unit.name: Eaton
sub_unit.note: The Pilot lists 113 votes for Gamaliel H. Barstow.

sub_unit.name: Niagara
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 1 vote as Samuel H. Payne.

sub_unit.name: Oneida
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 1 vote as Samuel Paine.
Gamaliel H. Barstow received 4 votes as Gamaiel Barstow, 1 vote as Gamaliel Barstow and 1 vote as Gamaliel H. Barstow, 1 vote as Gamaliel H. Barot and 1 vote as Gamaliel Briston.
David E. Evans received 1 vote as David I. Evans and 6 votes as Daniel E. Evans.
John Lincklean received 1 vote as John Linelean.
The Utica Patriot, and Patrol (Utica, NY), May 19, and the Columbian Gazette, May 12, list 1858 votes for David E. Evans, 1419 for Perry G. Childs, and 542 for Samuel Payne in Oneida county.

sub_unit.name: Ontario
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 1 vote as Samuel T. Payne.

sub_unit.name: Seneca
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 1 vote as Sam'l Payne.

sub_unit.name: Steuben
sub_unit.note: Gamaliel H. Barstow received 4 votes as Gamaliel Barstow.
David E. Evans received 1 vote as Daniel E. Evans.

sub_unit.name: Tompkins
sub_unit.note: Samuel Payne received 170 votes as Samuel S. Payne.
Gamaliel H. Barstow received 3 votes as Gamaliel G. Barstow.
"Landmarks of Tompkins County" lists 806 votes for David E. Evans, 720 for Gamaliel H. Barstow, 568 for Perry G. Childs, and 371 for Samuel Payne in Tompkins county.
